        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "improve(control-ui): expose linear session positions in chat picker",
        "body": "Related: #82450\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nResolves a first slice of the accessibility problem where blind and keyboard users navigating the existing Control UI chat session picker did not get a linear row position or a clear current-session cue from each session option.\n\nThis is intentionally related to #82450 rather than closing it: the larger Linear Persistent Workspace Mode still needs product decisions beyond this picker affordance.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe chat session picker now gives each loaded option a stable visible ordinal marker and an explicit accessible label that includes current-session state plus its position in the loaded list. This keeps the existing `sessions.list` search, pagination, filtering, and storage behavior unchanged.\n\nClawSweeper follow-up: the new current-session and loaded-list-position phrases are now routed through `chat.selectors.*` i18n keys, and the locale outputs/metadata were regenerated from the source bundle.\n\n## User Impact\n\nScreen-reader users can hear labels such as `Alpha planning, current session, session 1 of 2 in the loaded list` while navigating the picker, and sighted keyboard users get matching linear row numbers in the existing picker UI.\n\n## Evidence\n\nCurrent head: `9c1c301aa9fcb4f23dfc4b983856b7fe521282cc`\n\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n- `pnpm changed:lanes --json` reported `core=true`, `coreTests=true`, and no extension/app/docs lanes.\n- `pnpm ui:i18n:sync` with provider keys cleared regenerated 20 locale bundles from the English source bundle; the two new selector keys are present in every generated locale file and metadata record.\n- `pnpm ui:i18n:check` passed with the same local Windows formatter-path workaround used for sync; all 20 locales were clean with the two expected fallback keys.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts --reporter=verbose` passed: 1 file, 120 tests.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.ui-e2e.config.ts --configLoader runner ui/src/ui/e2e/chat-picker-pagination.e2e.test.ts` passed: 1 file, 2 tests.\n\nInspectable Control UI picker proof at current head:\n\n```text\nControl UI chat session picker after-fix proof\nbaseUrl: http://127.0.0.1:63121/\nbrowser: Chromium via Playwright\nsessions.list requests: 1\noptions:\n- key=agent:alpha position=1 visibleIndex=1 ariaSelected=true ariaLabel starts with \"Alpha planning, current session, session 1 of 2 in the loaded list\"\n- key=agent:design position=2 visibleIndex=2 ariaSelected=false ariaLabel starts with \"Design review, session 2 of 2 in the loaded list\"\nassertions:\n- visible ordinal markers matched positions: true\n- current option aria-label includes current-session cue: true\n- second option aria-label includes loaded-list position: true\n```\n\nLocal screenshot artifact captured and inspected from the same run: `.artifacts/control-ui-e2e/linear-session-picker/session-picker-linear-list-after-i18n.png`.\n\nEarlier branch proof before the i18n follow-up also passed Crabbox local-container in `mcr.microsoft.com/playwright:v1.60.0-noble`: provider `local-container`, lease `cbx_0f6a4116b612`, slug `violet-crayfish`, exit `0`. That run used a frozen install plus the same focused unit and UI E2E tests with the container Chromium path.\n",
